correctness.rationale: Largely ungrounded and schema-inconsistent. While some items are correct (ALD method = TALD; material ZnO; precursor DEZ and water; substrate SWNTs on TEM grids; temperature 200 °C; number of cycles = 37; nanoparticles amorphous by TEM), most values are not reported in the article and/or conflict with it. Key issues: (1) Schema violation: processParameters.plasmaPower is set to null although the type requires an object and PEALD was not used (this field should be omitted). (2) Fabricated/untraceable process parameters: pressure (0.1 mTorr), carrier/purging gas = Ar, delivery method, dosing times (100 ms), purge times (1000 ms), flow rates (10 “SCM-PER-MIN”), saturation (False), nucleationPeriod (5 cycles) – none are provided in the paper. (3) Thickness/GPC incorrect: growthPerCycle = 0.15 Å and filmThickness = 5.55 nm are not reported and contradict the article’s morphology (nanoparticles <3 nm after 37 cycles; no continuous film). (4) Material properties ungrounded: refractive index, absorption coefficient, band gap by UV-Vis, resistivity, carrier density, mobility, uniformity, conformality aspect ratio, roughness, and density (and its unit choice) are not measured/reported here; EDS only confirms presence of Zn and O — the quantitative elemental concentration (50%) and atomic ratio 1:1 are not given. (5) Device properties are incorrect and irrelevant: TFT metrics (mobility, Vt, SS, on/off, device structure) are not in this article; the device study is field emission, not TFT. (6) Multiple processes described in the article are not captured: besides 37 cycles at 200 °C, the authors also report 200 cycles at 200 °C and 70 cycles at 250 °C for field-emission samples; only one process was extracted. (7) Other untraceable entries: safety, film stability, reproducibility. These issues collectively make the extraction not traceable and in parts scientifically inconsistent. Properties to correct/remove: plasmaPower, pressure, carrier/purging gas, dosing/purge times, flow rates, GPC, film thickness, saturation, nucleation period, optical/electrical/uniformity/conformality/roughness/density values, film composition quantification, TFT device metrics; add separate processes for the 200-cycle and 70-cycle cases if extracted.

completeness.rationale: Very poor completeness and traceability. (1) Multiple processes in the article are not captured: ALD on suspended SWNTs at 200 °C for 37 cycles and for 200 cycles (Fig. 2), and a separate process used for field-emission samples at 250 °C for 70 cycles (sample II). Only one process (37 cycles at 200 °C) is represented. (2) Many values are fabricated and not supported by the text: carrier/purging gas type (Ar), reactor pressure, dosing/purge times, flow rates, growth-per-cycle, saturation, nucleation period, film thickness, uniformity, conformality aspect ratio, optical properties (refractive index, UV-Vis), electrical properties (Hall-derived resistivity, carrier density, mobility), roughness (AFM), film density (XRR), and all TFT deviceProperties. The article does not report these measurements. (3) Inconsistencies with the article: reporting a continuous film thickness (5.55 nm) and GPC (0.15 Å/cycle) for 37 cycles is not supported; the article shows discrete nanoparticles (<3 nm at 37 cycles; <5 nm at 200 cycles) rather than a film. The computed 5.55 nm also conflicts with the stated GPC (0.15 Å × 37 = 5.55 Å, not nm). Atomic ratio “1:1” and 50% elemental concentration from EDS are not reported; EDS is only qualitative (weak Zn and O). DeviceProperties (mobility, Vth, SS, on/off) are unrelated to this study (field emission, not TFTs). (4) Schema issues: plasmaPower is set to null, which violates the schema (non-PEALD should omit this field rather than set it to null). (5) What to add/review: extract separate process instances for 200 °C/37 cycles, 200 °C/200 cycles (suspended SWNTs), and 250 °C/70 cycles (sample II); keep only traceable fields (TALD, ZnO, DEZ, H2O, substrate description, temperatures, number of cycles, qualitative crystallinity from TEM, qualitative EDS evidence). Remove or leave unspecified optional fields that are not reported (pressure, dosing/purge times, flows, GPC, film thickness, optical/electrical/AFM/XRR/TFT metrics). Given the extent of non-traceable or incorrect values and missing processes, completeness is very poor.
